<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏰 Builder Basics — The Living Village (Extension)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Bring It All Together · <strong>Course:</strong> Builder Basics · <strong>Type:</strong> Extension Activity · <strong>Time:</strong> about 90 minutes</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧩 This is a bonus challenge, not a weekly lesson. Try it after <strong>Complete Your Village</strong>, once you can build with loops, move the agent between spots, and place water and animals.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · The Challenge 🎯</h2>
<p>You already finished a small village. Make one that feels <strong>alive</strong> — crops growing, animals wandering, water you can cross.</p>
<p>By the end, your village must have <strong>all eight</strong> of these:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🌾 A <strong>farm</strong> — rows of crops
🏠 A <strong>farm house</strong> — where the farmer lives
🗼 A <strong>house with a watchtower</strong> — a home with a tall tower on top
🧱 A <strong>fence</strong> — around the farm or the animals
💧 A <strong>pond with fish</strong> — water with a fish in it
🌉 A <strong>bridge</strong> — one that crosses over the pond
🪣 A <strong>well</strong> — for water
🐄 A <strong>few animals</strong> — cows, sheep, pigs, or chickens</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There is no fixed size and no map — <strong>you</strong> decide how big each thing is and where it goes. One rule you must not break:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>⚠️ <strong>Everything you can build must be built with code.</strong> No placing blocks by hand. (Animals are spawned — code or a spawn egg is fine.)</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>List the eight things your village must have when you finish.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>The last village was built with code. Why does building with code get <em>easier</em> the bigger your village gets?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Plan Before You Build ✏️</h2>
<p>A builder plans first. For <strong>each</strong> part, decide the blocks, the size, and whether a loop can do the repeating.</p>
<p><strong>Farm</strong> — What crop? How many rows, and how long is each row?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Farm house</strong> — What blocks for the walls and roof? How wide and how tall?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>House with a watchtower</strong> — Where does the tower sit — a corner, the middle, the roof? How much taller than the house is it?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Fence</strong> — What does it go around? How will the agent turn the corners?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pond with fish</strong> — How will you make the dip in the ground? What fills it, and where do the fish go?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bridge over the pond</strong> — How wide is the pond at its narrowest? How long must the bridge be to reach across?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Well</strong> — What shape is the hole? What goes around the top? Is there water inside?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Animals</strong> — Which animals, and how many? Will they go inside the fence?</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Think in Loops 🔁</h2>
<p>Eight structures is a lot to place one block at a time. A loop is for anything you do <strong>again and again</strong> — a row of crops, the four sides of a fence, the planks of a bridge, the levels of a tower.</p>
<p><strong>Pick three parts that will use a loop. For each one, say what the loop repeats each time.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p>Between one structure and the next, the agent has to <strong>walk to a new spot</strong> so nothing lands on top of the last build.</p>
<p><strong>After you build the farm house, how does the agent get to a clean spot to start the watchtower house?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p>The bridge and the fence are special: they change direction. A fence goes across, then <strong>turns</strong>, then goes across again.</p>
<p><strong>What has to happen to the agent between one side of the fence and the next?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Show Your Work 📸🎥</h2>
<p>Go to your homework world and build each part one at a time, moving the agent between them. Build the water first, then put the bridge across it so you can see it reach.</p>
<p>Keep going until your village has <strong>all eight</strong> parts — the farm, the farm house, the watchtower house, the fence, the pond with fish, the bridge, the well, and the animals.</p>
<p>Record <strong>one video</strong> — one take, no stopping (a phone is fine). Show these in order:</p>
<p><strong>1 · Your code.</strong> Scroll through it. Say what each part does.</p>
<p><strong>2 · Your build.</strong> Point the camera. Name the parts.</p>
<p>Fill the blanks:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Today I built ______.</p>
<p>I built it using this code: ______.</p>
<p>In this code I used ______.</p>
<p>The hardest part was ______.</p>
<p>That part was hard because ______.</p>
<p>The most fun part was ______.</p>
<p>Something new I learned was ______.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write your lines here, then say them in your video.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
